text.tspan: Create a unique avatar illustration using free Figma components.
Combine preset components or create your own and go wild.

Did you created cool new assets, and you don’t want to keep it for yourself? You can make your additions part of the official library! Just send us your updated Figma file, and we will update it. We can also mention you as a contributor if you want to.
• For using a Hijab you need to detach avatar component and swap head component layer with clothing one.

To customize the library simply go to the Components page in this document. We recommend duplicating existing components and use them as templates to create your own. You can also just edit the existing components and fine-tune them as you want.

To customize existing colors, just edit the color you want to change and update the layer style. For adding a new color, simply create a new layer with the color you like to add and create a new layer style.
We recommend using Scale Tool [K] to keep all the layers aligned perfectly and to maintain all proportions (rounded corners, border width). Resizing manually might brake some stuff.
Color of some instances can be overridden by using layer styles.
There are two different color types:
• Colors - for Clothes, Accessories and Background (17 options)
Every avatar has instances that you can apply. When you select an avatar, check out the layer section to see all the instances you can customize.
Go to the Assets menu “avatar” and choose between circular, squared or squared with frame background. You can override the color of the background by using layer styles.
Be careful switching from Default to Circle, since you will lose your overrides!
• In the Current File section, click “Publish”
High-quality Lottie animations and static SVG illustrations that will delight your project.
